The Yobe State Police Command on Sunday, confirmed the killing of a commercial sex worker, Stella aka Ritachi, at Dorawa Joint, in Potiskum Local Government Area of the State.
The command’s Spokesman, ASP Dungus Abdulkarim, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Damaturu, the state capital, that Stella was stabbed to death by unidentified persons in her room, at the joint located in Yindiski Ward. “The incident was believed to have occurred at about 6:40 pm on Saturday, and the splattered blood all over the room indicated that the assailants might had struggled with the victim,” he said. I was sexually molested – Stella Damascus The spokesman said five other commercial sex workers (names withheld) in the compound were arrested for interrogation. “They should have some information for us because the deceased must have shouted during the apparent struggle with the killers,” he said. Abdulkarim added that the case had been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department (SCIID) for investigation. Angry mob attack alleged crazy killer of teenage boy